HEADWORD: Speed counter
<hw>Speed counter</hw>. <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>A device for
automatically counting the revolutions or pulsations of an engine or
other machine; -- called also simply
<altname>counter</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

